description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;We are thrilled to offer new opportunities for Band 5 nurses wishing to gain experience and develop skills in our new Oxford Health Band 5 Nurse rotational scheme. The 2 year programme consists of two 9 month and one 6 month rotation including: Eating Disorders, CAMHS inpatient services, Psychiatric Intensive Care, Adult of Working Age In both in patients and Community settings and in Older Adult inpatient and community settings. There is potential for expansion of rotations in the future within our ambitious plans making this an exciting opportunity to consolidate knowledge and skills, and further your career.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;These rotational posts will offer the opportunity to work across different mental health pathways, developing medication management competence, assessment and leadership skills and will provide you with a career that is varied and interesting, as well as earn more money if you choose to work additional hours as part of our own staff bank.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;We are happy to support newly qualified or experienced nurses within our rotations. We can offer professional support consisting of:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;A comprehensive induction &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Preceptorship and Flyer programme for newly qualified nurses&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;A structured In-Service Training programme&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Outstanding supervision and Personal Development support from inspiring clinical leaders &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Group supervision and in house training sessions bespoke to your needs &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Opportunities to embark on further educational module courses with Master’s degree accreditation&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;At the end of the 2 year rotation and following successful completion of competencies, there will be opportunities to progress to vacant Band 6 posts.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameNatalie CleavelandJob titleHead of NursingEmail addressNatalie.Cleaveland@Oxfordhealth.nhs.ukTelephone number07747753095Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;We would encourage you to give us a call to discuss the role and we very much welcome visits from interested applicants.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;For more information or to arrange an informal visit please contact: Natalie Cleveland, Head of Nursing on 07747 753095, Carol Gee, Matron (Adult Inpatients) on 07773 761582 or Sue Lucas, Service Manager (Older Adult and Adult Community) on 07768 946631&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
